description:
"Different Perspectives on the Role of Culture in International Affairs" by Erik Nemeth at the 2016 Gray Area Festival

Illicit trade of cultural artifacts from war-torn and destabilized areas has dramatic implications for state security and cultural heritage preservation. Digital tools provide new ways of engaging with cultural artifacts, at the same time raising important issues around preservation, neo-colonialism, and digital authenticity. 

The Gray Area Festival is four days of conference, performances, workshops, and exhibitions to discuss the impact of art and technology on culture. More at http://grayareafestival.io
